caption:
I’ve been thinking a lot about the future of mobility, and was delighted to have the opportunity to visit the Bharat Mobility Expo 2025, on invitation from @marutisuzukiofficial 🌱

At Maruti’s sustainability zone, I witnessed: 

👉🏼 The launch of their first EV - e VITARA, an electric SUV. 

👉🏼 A prototype of a market-ready, mass category WagonR run on flex fuel - that can run on upto 85% ethanol made from crop waste. 

👉🏼 A small flying car powered by batteries, that might just feature in the future of private transport! 

When it comes to the clean transport transition, there are no silver bullet solutions. We need multiple technologies and approaches for different segments. Feeling hopeful having seen a glimpse of what the future of cars might look like! 

How do you think cars are going to transform in the near future?

Follow @shivya for more discussions on conscious travel and living 🌱
